{"body": "Triage:

Root cause: The exponential backoff counter is stored in worker-local in-memory state, not persisted/shared across process recycles. When a worker recycles (e.g., during a deploy or scaling event), its backoff counter resets to zero. Under sustained upstream 5xx errors, all recycled workers then immediately retry at the minimum backoff interval simultaneously, producing a thundering-herd retry storm instead of a gradual backoff.

Priority: P1 — this amplifies outages (turns transient upstream 5xx blips into self-inflicted retry storms that can take down otherwise-recovering upstreams), but it requires a specific trigger (worker recycle during an upstream error storm) rather than being an always-on failure.", "issue_id": "issue-1"}

{"body": "Triage:

Root cause: Not a bug — this is a feature gap. The migration CLI currently has no --dry-run mode, so there's no way to preview planned schema changes before they're applied, making it hard to review migrations safely in CI prior to staging.

Priority: P2 — valuable for review safety and CI workflow, but no active defect or user-facing failure; can be scheduled as normal feature work.", "issue_id": "issue-3"}
